- **Billing**: Stripe (subscriptions + webhooks)
- **Email**: Resend (transactional emails)
- **Tooling**: Biome + Oxlint + Lefthook

## Getting Started

### 1. Install Dependencies

```bash
bun install
```

### 2. Set Up Environment Variables

Copy `.env.local.example` to `.env.local` and fill in your keys:

```bash
cp .env.local.example .env.local
```

You'll need:
- **Convex**: Deployment URL (auto-configured on first run)
- **GitHub OAuth**: Client ID and secret from [GitHub Developer Settings](https://github.com/settings/developers)
- **Stripe**: Secret key and webhook secret from [Stripe Dashboard](https://dashboard.stripe.com)
- **Resend**: API key from [Resend Dashboard](https://resend.com)

### 3. Start Development

```bash
# Start Convex backend (opens dashboard on first run)
bunx convex dev

# In another terminal, start the frontend
bun run dev
```

